In my opinion the Sanskrit text, "Satyam bruyat priyam bruyat, Na bruyat
satyam apriyam" means that one should speak the truth in gentle language. One
had better not speak it, if one cannot do so in a gentle way; meaning
thereby that there is no truth in a man who cannot control his toungue.
